   abstract = {In this study we have shown that in humans it is possible to monitor non-invasively and simultaneously both hemispheres revealing cortical oxygenation changes in the occipital area in response to a contra-lateral hemi-ﬁeld paradigm. A novel multi-channel near infrared spectroscopy approach with a high temporal resolution was used. The results conﬁrm previous ﬁndings obtained by functional magnetic resonance imaging and positron emission tomography with the advantage to measure directly not only concentration changes in deoxyhemoglobin as measured by functional magenetic resonance imaging (MRI), but also in oxyhemoglobin with low cost instrumentation potentially useful to investigate the pathophysiology of vision. ©2000 Elsevier Science Ltd. All rights reserved.},
